original_client_text.markup_text:
A comforting, cheesy keto casserole packed with tender chicken, fresh broccoli, and crispy bacon. The perfect easy weeknight dinner that the whole family will love.

üìä Per serving (Serves 6):
Calories: 320
Protein: 18g
Fat: 26g
Carbs: 5g
Fiber: 2g
Net Carbs: 3g

Prep Time: 15 mins
Cook Time: 30 mins
Total Time: 45 mins

üõí Ingredients:
Chicken Base:
‚Ä¢ 3 cups cooked chicken, shredded
‚Ä¢ 4 cups broccoli florets
‚Ä¢ 8 slices bacon, cooked and chopped
‚Ä¢ 1 cup cheddar cheese, shredded
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded

Creamy Sauce:
‚Ä¢ 8 oz cream cheese, softened
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup heavy cream
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup chicken broth
‚Ä¢ 2 tbsp butter
‚Ä¢ 2 garlic cloves, minced
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp onion powder
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp dried thyme
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp salt
‚Ä¢ 1/4 tsp black pepper
‚Ä¢ Pinch of nutmeg

Topping:
‚Ä¢ 1 cup cheddar cheese, shredded
‚Ä¢ 2 tbsp parmesan cheese, grated
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp fresh parsley, chopped
‚Ä¢ Red pepper flakes (optional)

üë©‚Äçüç≥ Instructions:
Prep:
1. Preheat oven to 375¬∞F
2. Grease 9x13 baking dish
3. Cook and shred chicken
4. Blanch broccoli 2 minutes
5. Cook and chop bacon

Sauce:
1. In saucepan, melt butter
2. Add garlic, cook 30 seconds
3. Add cream cheese, stir until melted
4. Whisk in heavy cream and broth
5. Add seasonings

Assembly:
1. Layer chicken in baking dish
2. Add broccoli florets
3. Pour sauce over evenly
4. Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese
5. Add half the bacon

Baking:
1. Cover with foil
2. Bake 20 minutes
3. Remove foil
4. Add remaining cheese
5. Bake 10 more minutes

Final Touch:
1. Broil 2-3 minutes
2. Until golden and bubbly
3. Remove from oven
4. Top with remaining bacon
5. Sprinkle with parsley

To Serve:
1. Let stand 5 minutes
2. Cut into portions
3. Garnish with red pepper flakes
4. Serve hot
5. Add extra cheese if desired

#ketocasserole #lowcarbdinner #chickenbroccoli #easyketo #ketochickencasserole #ketodinner
